TITLE: New York police hunting for Long Island gunman who wounded 3 during shooting at luxury hotel pool party
SUMMARY: Three people suffered non-life-threatening injuries when they were shot after a dispute at an upscale Long Island hotel and event space during a pool party, police said.

TITLE: Maryland police warn of 'grandparent scam', launch hunt for suspect
SUMMARY: Police in Maryland are asking for the public’s help in tracking down the mastermind of a “grandparent scam” that has targeted at least three elderly people.

TITLE: Dead humpback whale washes up in New Jersey
SUMMARY: The 25-foot-long carcass of a juvenile humpback whale washed up in the Grassy Sound Marina in North Wildwood, New Jersey, over the weekend. It was unclear how the whale died.

TITLE: California police arrest woman for allegedly setting man on fire with gasoline
SUMMARY: Police in Sanger, California arrested a woman for allegedly setting a man on fire at a local park on Saturday. Police have not announced what the woman's motive was.

TITLE: California forest fire rages on as firefighters protect the Yosemite sequoia trees
SUMMARY: A heat wave in California continued as firefighters battled a wildfire that has been posing a threat to the giant sequoias and a small community in Yosemite National Park.

TITLE: Wanted Kentucky police shooter is shot in Louisville park
SUMMARY: A Kentucky man who fired on a police officer has been shot. The officer was shot in the chest but was wearing a bulletproof vest and is in stable condition.

TITLE: Yosemite fire grows as crews protect iconic sequoias
SUMMARY: California firefighters battled a wildfire in Yosemite National Park Sunday that nearly doubled in size in a day in an effort to protect the iconic trees and nearby town.

TITLE: Connecticut teen dead, woman injured in Fairfield
SUMMARY: A Connecticut teenager was killed and a woman was wounded in a shooting at a Fairfield church on Saturday. The shooting came after a fight broke out at the church banquet hall.

TITLE: Georgia man shot dead at gas station while trying to stop suspects from stealing his car, police say
SUMMARY: A man killed in a shooting at a gas station in Peachtree Corners, Georgia, was trying to stop suspected carjackers from stealing his vehicle, authorities said.

TITLE: Kansas City bar shooting leads to 1 dead, 5 injured
SUMMARY: A Kansas City bar was the site of a recent shooting which left 1 dead and 5 people injured. Off duty police officers were working the security at the time of the shooting.

TITLE: Man injured in shootout in Chicago parking lot, minutes after a woman is carjacked less than a mile away
SUMMARY: Five gunmen surrounded a concealed-carry holder in a Chicago parking lot and a shoot out ensued minutes after a woman was carjacked less than a mile away.

TITLE: Massachusetts Legislative leaders announce $500M in tax relief proposals
SUMMARY: Massachusetts leaders announced plans for a $500 million tax relief package that includes an increase in credits for older residents, lower-income workers, as well as parents.

TITLE: San Francisco schools used over $500K marked for improvements to remove 'offensive' Washington mural
SUMMARY: Critics sued the San Francisco School district over it use of over $500k in bond funding to defend lawsuits over its decision to cover a mural of George Washington.

TITLE: As midterms approach, suburban women share top voting priorities
SUMMARY: Suburban women in Loudoun County, Virginia, shared their top priorities when considering candidates to vote for in the 2022 midterm elections this November.

TITLE: Wisconsin parents charged after their child dies of fentanyl poisoning
SUMMARY: The parents of a child who died after accidently ingested fentanyl are being charged with child neglect. The fentanyl belonged to the father.

TITLE: Florida man tries to outrun deputies on riding lawnmower, authorities say
SUMMARY: Theft suspect Dusty Mobley, 40, was arrested in Holt, Florida, after switching a John Deere riding lawnmower "into high gear" and trying to outrun deputies, authorities said.

TITLE: Texas police make arrest in cold double murder case after 17 years
SUMMARY: Police in Texas believe they have solved a 17-year-old cold murder case in which two elderly people were killed in 2005. The breakthrough came from DNA on a bloody rug.

TITLE: Sea lions chase away beachgoers in San Diego, viral video shows
SUMMARY: Visitors at Ja Jolla Cove in San Diego, California, were sent running when two salty sea lions chased them away after a witness said one tourist got too close to the animals.

TITLE: Police searching for suspects after man stabbed in Times Square
SUMMARY: A group of three to four men reportedly stabbed a 41-year-old man in Times Square early Monday morning. Police are searching for suspects but have not released details.
